# Akashi code review (global)

The **code review agent** instructions for this project are maintained in your **global Cursor user configuration**, not duplicated here.

**Where to find them**

- **On this machine:** `~/.cursor/rules/code-review-agent.mdc` (same content as the former project rule).
- **Cursor UI:** **Cursor Settings → Rules, Commands → User rules** — if your build does not load `~/.cursor/rules` automatically, open that file and paste or sync its body into a User rule so Agent (Chat) picks it up everywhere.

**Scope:** The global rule has no file globs; Cursor applies it when Agent judges it relevant from the description, or when you @mention it. If you want it tied to `src/**` in this repo only, duplicate or symlink a project rule with `globs` under `.cursor/rules`.

For collaborators: add the same user rule (or keep a copy under `.cursor/rules` in the repo) so reviews stay consistent.

## TypeScript: imports at the top

- All static `import` / `import type` declarations belong at the **top** of the file (before any other statements). **No** mid-file imports.
- Prefer top-level `import type { … } from "…"` over inline `import("…").Type` in type positions when it expresses the same dependency.
- Use dynamic `import()` only for real lazy-loading of runtime modules, not as a substitute for organizing type imports.

The same bullets are mirrored in the global user rule `~/.cursor/rules/code-review-agent.mdc` under **Code quality** and **Common issues**.
